<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Betroth" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Betroth,</orth> to affiance: <cit><quote>--ed her to County Paris,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.238" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 3, 238</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--s himself to unquietness,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 1.3.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 3, 49</bibl></cit>. Generally in the partic. <emph>--ed</emph>: <cit><quote>to whom I am --ed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.2.111" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. IV, 2, 111</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.1.177" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. IV, 1, 177</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 5.270" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. V, 270</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.5.26" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 5, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.181" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 7, 181</bibl>. <cit><quote>we are --ed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.4.179" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. II, 4, 179</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--ed lovers,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.4.108" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 4, 108</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.406" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 406</bibl>. <cit><quote>his old --ed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.293" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 293</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.286" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 286</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>